{"parentUuid":"055e40aa-a97a-4ac4-a358-6ba922a70ebd","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"a273d6c6-461f-42c6-a353-672fd3d0ded5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a9b2481835b95795d","slug":"cozy-foraging-pie","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012KFqJw4tB2fJbyoh3MkvzY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 27\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/27](https://www.erdosproblems.com/27)\n    23→\n    24→An $\\varepsilon$-almost covering system is a set of congruences $a_i \\pmod{n_i}$ for distinct\n    25→moduli $n_1 < \\cdots < n_k$ such that the natural density of integers satisfying none of them\n    26→is at most $\\varepsilon$.\n    27→\n    28→Erdős asked whether there exists a constant $C > 1$ such that for every $\\varepsilon > 0$ and\n    29→$N \\geq 1$, there is an $\\varepsilon$-almost covering system with $N \\leq n_1 < \\cdots < n_k \\leq CN$.\n    30→This was disproved by Filaseta, Ford, Konyagin, Pomerance, and Yu [FFKPY07].\n    31→\n    32→[FFKPY07] Filaseta, M., Ford, K., Konyagin, S., Pomerance, C., and Yu, G.,\n    33→_Sieving by large integers and covering systems of congruences_.\n    34→Journal of the American Mathematical Society (2007), 495-517.\n    35→-/\n    36→\n    37→open Finset\n    38→\n    39→open scoped Classical\n    40→\n    41→namespace Erdos27\n    42→\n    43→/-- A congruence system has distinct moduli if no two pairs share the same modulus. -/\n    44→def HasDistinctModuli (S : Finset (ℤ × ℕ)) : Prop :=\n    45→  S.card = (S.image Prod.snd).card\n    46→\n    47→/-- The LCM of all moduli in a congruence system. -/\n    48→noncomputable def systemLcm (S : Finset (ℤ × ℕ)) : ℕ :=\n    49→  (S.image Prod.snd).lcm id\n    50→\n    51→/--\n    52→The density of uncovered integers for a congruence system, measured as the proportion of\n    53→integers in $\\{0, \\ldots, L-1\\}$ not covered by any congruence, where $L$ is the LCM of\n    54→all moduli.\n    55→-/\n    56→noncomputable def uncoveredDensity (S : Finset (ℤ × ℕ)) : ℝ :=\n    57→  let L := systemLcm S\n    58→  ((Finset.range L).filter (fun x =>\n    59→    ∀ p ∈ S, ¬((↑p.2 : ℤ) ∣ (↑x - p.1)))).card / (L : ℝ)\n    60→\n    61→/--\n    62→There is no constant $C > 1$ such that for every $\\varepsilon > 0$ and $N \\geq 1$, there\n    63→exists an $\\varepsilon$-almost covering system whose moduli all lie in the interval $[N, CN]$.\n    64→\n    65→Erdős conjectured this was possible; it was disproved by Filaseta, Ford, Konyagin,\n    66→Pomerance, and Yu [FFKPY07].\n    67→-/\n    68→@[category research solved, AMS 11]\n    69→theorem erdos_27 :\n    70→    answer(False) ↔\n    71→    ∃ C : ℝ, C > 1 ∧\n    72→      ∀ ε : ℝ, ε > 0 →\n    73→      ∀ N : ℕ, N ≥ 1 →\n    74→      ∃ S : Finset (ℤ × ℕ),\n    75→        HasDistinctModuli S ∧\n    76→        S.Nonempty ∧\n    77→        (∀ p ∈ S, p.2 ≥ 2) ∧\n    78→        (∀ p ∈ S, N ≤ p.2 ∧ (p.2 : ℝ) ≤ C * N) ∧\n    79→        uncoveredDensity S ≤ ε := by\n    80→  sorry\n    81→\n    82→end Erdos27\n    83→"}]},"uuid":"dc0c09fa-4384-4c76-99a7-74d948d00a55","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:07:07.221Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"055e40aa-a97a-4ac4-a358-6ba922a70ebd"}
{"parentUuid":"dc0c09fa-4384-4c76-99a7-74d948d00a55","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"a273d6c6-461f-42c6-a353-672fd3d0ded5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a9b2481835b95795d","slug":"cozy-foraging-pie","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0189UanbYEPvw97wvGFHDo7x","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I found the file for Erdos Problem 27.\n\n**File Path:** `/home/ryan/formal-conjectures/FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/27.lean`\n\n**File Contents:**\n\nThe file contains the Lean formalization of Erdős Problem 27, which concerns ε-almost covering systems. The problem asks whether there exists a constant C > 1 such that for every ε > 0 and N ≥ 1, there is an ε-almost covering system whose moduli all lie in the interval [N, CN]. This was disproved by Filaseta, Ford, Konyagin, Pomerance, and Yu in 2007.\n\nThe file defines:\n- `HasDistinctModuli`: A predicate ensuring the system has distinct moduli\n- `systemLcm`: The LCM of all moduli in a system\n- `uncoveredDensity`: The density of integers not covered by any congruence in the system\n- `erdos_27`: The main theorem stating the answer is False (the constant C does not exist)\n\nThe theorem is currently left as `sorry` (unproven)."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1764,"cache_read_input_tokens":12818,"output_tokens":273,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1764},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYt7JRScoDkNP48Ni9fYD","type":"assistant","uuid":"dce2eff4-c1cf-4a83-afa2-a43ab2e50313","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:07:10.149Z"}
